The atmosphere at Tajin was beautiful from the lighting fixtures to the paintings and decor.  The first impression was wonderful in this casual yet sizable and bright restaurant only to be upstaged by the food and the attentive staff.  I had the chicken chimichanga which was light and crispy on the outside and savory and juicy inside.  My wife had the fish tacos, the fish was not fried.  It  had a delightful char on the outside and the center was delicate.  This family owned restaurant has some of the best Mexican food around!  Not too heavy, tough, or over fried.  The portions were a good size, leaving us satisfied.  We had a great experience and look forward to returning!

This is our go to favorite lunch place for delicious, cooked to order, fresh Mexican food! Be prepared to wait for your food to be served and do not complain about it! This is a family run restaurant that services numerous people per day in the Downtown/Financial district and I am one of them. We go there on our lunch break and those days are special! You know like Monday, or Wednesday, any day of the week. They are super warm and friendly, they work hard, but they put out the best authentic dishes before you. You actually crave their chimichangas! A nice menu with plenty of choices. Their guacamole in the tiny tortilla bowl melts in your mouth. They serve ice cold, cinnamony horchatas in a mason jar that will blow your mind! They have a full service bar, but, you can only consume alcohol downstairs. Their margaritas are the only ones I can drink on the rocks- smooth and delicious with a perfect balance of tequila and who am I kidding, you can taste the tequila!! Thats all that matters! They can deliver to your office, but why would you want that? Go there! Make room in your schedule. They are newly renovated since last year and we can't stay away! Adios!!

The food was so good, we got burritos and nachos and then also chips and guacamole!(we love our guac) and the edible bowl idea is fab!! Would 1000 percent come back here if we were in this area again/visiting nyc again!!!

First impression was a nice place, however the wall opposite from bar reeked of mold and bad humidity. As a Mexican person myself, there food was a little bland. My chimichanga didn't come with white cheese sauce on top(original recipe) and when I asked they said it was inside. All I got was mozzarella cheese and no cheese sauce. Milanesa (breaded thin chicken) was very bland needed salt to start with.  I'd give another try.

Everything I have had here is delicious, and the staff is very accommodating.  I have the gene that makes cilantro taste like soap (or worse than soap really), and they’re always willing to help me find something that will work, and wherever possible have made adjustments.  You also get a ton of food.  Great local spot, and can’t beat the prices.
